1008 /* Clone data File state transfer.
1009 [FILE_STATE_NORMAL] --> [FILE_STATE_CLONED]
1010 Remote data is cloned into another file named <file_name>.clone.
1011
1012 [FILE_STATE_CLONED] --> [FILE_STATE_CLONE_SAVED]
1013 Before recovery the datafile is saved in a file named <file_name>.save.
1014
1015 [FILE_STATE_CLONE_SAVED] --> [FILE_STATE_REPLACED]
1016 Before recovery the cloned file is moved to datafile.
1017
1018 [FILE_STATE_REPLACED] --> [FILE_STATE_NORMAL]
1019 After successful recovery the saved data file is removed.
1020
1021 Every state transition involves a single file create, delete or rename and
1022 we consider them atomic. In case of a failure the state rolls back exactly
1023 in reverse order.
1024 */
